<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING - VALVE
        ROTATORS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="2">
        <title>VALVE ROTATORS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cleaning</title>
            <para>Clean rotators in a clean solvent.</para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspection</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Engines using roller tappets require a larger diameter valve rotator than those used on
                        engines with flat valve tappets. Refer to
                        <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150401.xml" xrefid="hl4150401">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>
                        for dimensions.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To properly test the rotator for function, a valve spring load must be applied to the
                    rotator.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The rotator must be lubricated with clean engine oil prior to testing.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the valve spring with the rotator in the spring tester
                    <emph type="bold">SE-2241</emph>. Place a ball bearing between the rotator and ram of the spring
                    tester. The ball bearing must be large enough to prevent the ram from touching any part of rotator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Paint a reference line on the rotator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Compress the valve spring rapidly with even pressure and observe the rotator as it
                    turns. (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150457">4.57</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    )
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace any rotator which does NOT turn.</para>
                <figure id="ef4150456" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11150" filename="../figcg1/cg11150.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.56. Checking Valve Spring Tension Using SE-2241.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150457" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10654" filename="../figcg1/cg10654.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.57. Test Valve Rotator.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
